'''Creampie''' (also known as '''internal [[ejaculation]]''' and, in [[Homosexuality|same-sex]] contexts, as '''breeding''' and '''seeding''') is a [[sexual act]], commonly featured in [[pornography]], in which a male [[Ejaculation|ejaculates]] inside his partner's [[vagina]] or [[Human anus|anus]] without use of a [[condom]], resulting in visible seeping or dripping of [[semen]] from the vagina or anus.<ref name=Carroll>{{cite book|title=Popular modernity in America: experience, technology, mythohistory|publisher=[[SUNY Press]]|author=Michael Thomas Carroll |year=2000|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fzSrmR1PRO0C|isbn=978-0-7914-4713-0|page=119}}</ref><ref name=Partridge>{{cite book|title=The New Partridge Dictionary of Slang and Unconventional English: A-I|publisher=[[Taylor & Francis]]|author1=Eric Partridge |author2=Tom Dalzell |author3=Terry Victor |year=2006|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4YfsEgHLjboC|isbn=978-0-415-25937-8|page=507}}</ref><ref name=Creed>{{cite book|title=Media matrix: sexing the new reality|publisher=[[Allen & Unwin]]|author=Barbara Creed |year=2003|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HhMBgOzMUpQC|isbn=978-1-86508-926-3|page=61}}</ref>

==Use in pornography==
[[File:Creampie drawing 1-2.png|thumb|Creampie: semen flowing out of a woman's vagina after sexual activity without a [[condom]]]]
Internal ejaculation shots are a comparatively recent development in pornography; they are not found in early pornographic films.<ref name="Thompson2007">{{cite book|author=Dave Thompson |title=Black and white and blue: adult cinema from the Victorian age to the VCR|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rBP6yjQwT8QC&pg=PA108|accessdate=13 December 2010|date=1 September 2007|publisher=ECW Press|isbn=978-1-55022-791-8|pages=108}}</ref> The use of the word ''creampie'' to describe such scenes originated in U.S. pornography in the early 2000s.<ref name=Partridge/><ref name="DalzellPartridge2008">{{cite book|author1=Tom Dalzell|author2=Eric Partridge|title=The Routledge dictionary of modern American slang and unconventional English|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5F-YNZRv-VMC&pg=PA248|accessdate=29 September 2010|year=2008|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0-415-37182-7|pages=248}}</ref>

Internal ejaculations, followed by images of semen dripping from the anus, are sometimes depicted in [[Bareback (sex)|bareback]] [[gay pornography]], where they are referred to by the term ''breeding'' or the ''reverse [[cum shot|money shot]]''.<ref name="Dean2009">{{cite book|author=Tim Dean|authorlink=Tim Dean|title=Unlimited intimacy: reflections on the subculture of barebacking|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0TA9YJ-QHn8C&pg=PA170|accessdate=29 September 2010|date=1 June 2009|publisher=University of Chicago Press|isbn=978-0-226-13939-5|pages=85, 135–136, 169–171}}</ref><ref name="Dean144">{{cite book|author=Tim Dean|authorlink=Tim Dean|title=Unlimited intimacy: reflections on the subculture of barebacking|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0TA9YJ-QHn8C&pg=PA144|accessdate=29 September 2010|date=1 June 2009|publisher=University of Chicago Press|isbn=978-0-226-13939-5|page=144}}</ref> Breeding is sometimes followed by [[felching]], which involves sucking the semen from the partner's anus.<ref name="Dean2009" />

In straight pornography, sexual activity is often followed by a [[facial (sex act)|facial]], [[Pearl necklace (sexuality)|pearl necklace]] or other visible ejaculation.<ref name="Dean2009" /> Creampie scenes depart from heterosexual pornographic convention in favor of a depiction that more closely mimics sexual activity as performed in ordinary life;<ref name="Dean2009" /> they have been called the "counterimage" of facials.<ref name=Carroll/> Perhaps following the example set by gay pornography, they have become a popular subgenre within heterosexual pornography since the turn of the century, featuring both vaginal and anal ejaculations.<ref name="DalzellPartridge2008" /><ref name="Dean2009" /><ref name=Kick /> In some creampie films, both gay and straight, sexual activity, including internal ejaculation, are followed by performers licking up the semen that has dripped from their bodies.<ref name="DalzellPartridge2008" />  Some pornographic films use an artificial semen substitute to simulate or enhance creampie shots.<ref name=Partridge/><ref name=Creed/>

Examples of heterosexual pornographic film series featuring creampies include ''Cream Filled Teens'' and ''Internal Cumbustion''.<ref name=Kick>{{cite book|title=Disinformation book of lists: subversive facts and hidden information in rapid-fire format|publisher=[[The Disinformation Company]]|author=[[Russ Kick|Russell Kick]] |year=2004|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=utssHzXYsWoC|isbn=978-0-9729529-4-1|page=192}}</ref> In male homosexual pornography, [[Treasure Island Media]] is a notable representative, its title ''Breed Me'' (1999) having been noted as one of the "earliest and most notorious" in the genre.<ref name="Dean2009" />

==Health risks==
The production of pornography featuring internal ejaculations involves [[unprotected sex]], increasing the risk of pregnancy in women and [[sexually transmitted infections]] (STIs/STDs) such as [[HIV]].<ref name="Dean2009"/> The risk of STIs is markedly increased in anal ejaculations.<ref name="Dean2009" />

In 2004, in a much publicized case, novice pornographic actress [[Lara Roxx]] contracted multiple infections, including HIV, from [[Darren James]] while filming a scene featuring an anal creampie.<ref name="Dean2009" /><ref>Craig Wingate, Anisha Moore-Johnson, Rheena Yangson, and Jason Lim (2006): [http://craigwingate.efolioworld.com/EvidenceofCompetence2/4f94bf43-da41-4221-afd7-2175b55c2ac3 ''Lights, Camera, Action: Safety on the Set! Empowerment Training for Adult Film Stars'']</ref> James had contracted HIV from having unprotected anal sex with a woman while on a trip to [[Brazil]]. He had tested negative for HIV after his return from the trip and infected three out of 13 actresses he worked with before testing positive in a subsequent test and ceasing to perform.<ref name="Dean97-100">{{cite book|author=Tim Dean|authorlink=Tim Dean|title=Unlimited intimacy: reflections on the subculture of barebacking|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0TA9YJ-QHn8C&pg=PA97|accessdate=29 September 2010|date=1 June 2009|publisher=University of Chicago Press|isbn=978-0-226-13939-5|pages=97–100}}</ref>

