{{Infobox museum | name = Universeum | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = Universeum2.JPG | imagesize = | caption = | alt = | map_type = | map_caption = | map_alt = | established = 2001 | location = [[Gothenburg]], [[Sweden]] | type = Public science centre, including [[zoo]] and [[Public aquarium|aquarium]]; Museum | collection = | visitors = | director = | president = | curator = | owner = | publictransit = | car_park = | network = | website = {{URL|http://www.universeum.se}} }}
'''Universeum''' is a public science centre and museum in [[Gothenburg]], [[Sweden]] that opened in 2001. It is a part of ''Evenemangsstråket'', the ''thoroughfare of events'' – close to [[Korsvägen]] and Skånegatan – which includes sights of interest like [[Scandinavium]], [[Ullevi]], [[Svenska Mässan]] (Swedish Exhibition Centre), [[Liseberg]] and the [[Museum of World Culture]].
Universeum is divided into six sections, each containing experiment workshops and a collection of [[reptile]]s, [[fish]] and [[insect]]s. Universeum occasionally gives Swedish secondary school students a chance to debate with [[Nobel prize]]-winners and professors.
==Main sections== [[Image:Goeldis monkey - butterfly lunch - big.jpg|thumb|[[Goeldi's marmoset]] run free in the ''Regnskogen'' area.]] The sections of Universeum are: * "Kalejdo" - An exhibit about Crime-investigation, [[laser]], [[space]], and more. * "Explora" - An experiment department that is mostly about humans and technology. * "Vattnets Väg" (Water's Way) - The Swedish fresh and [[brackish]] water fishes, reptiles and [[vole]]s. * "Akvariehallen" (The Ocean Zone) - Marine animals. This includes a {{convert|1400000|l|USgal}} Ocean Tank with sharks and other tropical fish,<ref>Universeum: ''[http://www.universeum.se/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=71&Itemid=82 The Ocean Tank.]'' Retrieved 30 June 2014.</ref> a {{convert|16|m|ft}} long aquarium with native marine fish,<ref>Universeum: ''[http://www.universeum.se/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=72&Itemid=83&lang=en The Swedish West Coast Aquarium.]'' Retrieved 30 June 2014.</ref> and a touch tank with [[Batoidea|rays]].<ref>Universeum: ''[http://www.universeum.se/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=69&Itemid=81 The Ray Tank.]'' Retrieved 30 June 2014.</ref> * "Regnskogen" (The Rainforest) - A rainforest hall with tropical animals.<ref>Universeum: ''[http://www.universeum.se/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=77&Itemid=86 The Rainforest.]'' Retrieved 30 June 2014.</ref> * "Dödliga Skönheter" (Deadly Beauties) - Deadly and venomous reptiles.
The architect behind Universeum is [[Gert Wingårdh]].
